Public schools in urban areas are full of both boys and girls.
Job opportunities must be provided to these young people, who will not want to return to the obscurantism of the old parties or to the corruption of some leaders.
Everyone, including armed militants, loves mobile phones, television, and Turkish soap operas that represent the modern world, and that are watched everywhere.
At the moment, there is an army.
Will the authorities that will command it be considered legitimate?
The old commanders who waged the anti-Soviet struggle are already taking steps to restore provincial militias that would not be subordinate to the central government.
Afghanistan, a mountainous country with strong local differences, should be decentralized to a certain extent, along the lines of Western countries, but the United States wanted to turn it into a centralized state with strong presidential power, eliminating the post of prime minister that had existed since the 1964 Constitution.
President Karzai does not want foreign control, especially in the run-up to the April 2014 elections.
