"He never goes out of fashion because his sketches are real works of art," she concludes.
Pedigree parade
Garavani's life is not a story of obsession, but of fully reciprocated love.
He loves people with good upbringing and high titles, and they love him.
One of Somerset House's galleries has been transformed into a glamorous catwalk of sixty metres in length that offers a change of roles: a visitor takes the place of a model and has to defile down the catwalk, contemplating the "audience" of dreams that gleam with Valentino masterpieces, such as the dress that Jacqueline Kennedy chose for her wedding to Aristotle Onassis, the suit used by Monica Vitti in "The Nights," or the wool and leather coat that belonged to Empress Fara Diba.
Names such as Sybille of Luxembourg, Gloria von Thurn und Taxis, Mette-Marit of Norway, Rosario of Bulgaria or Sophia Habsburg shine in this crowd of models.
Naty Abascal and fashion designer, in 2006
