Hector "Hetin" Reyes: "Basketball was my life"
An avid basketball traveler, Hector "Hetin" Reyes was associated with the sport for more than 60 years and, thanks to it, traveled the world.
Few people in Puerto Rico have as many basketball stories as Héctor "Hetin" Reyes.
Reyes was immersed in the sport for more than 60 years before a brain haemorrhage forced him to use a wheelchair in 2008, as a minor league player, Major League Basketball player, BSN representative and manager with the Bayamón Cowboys, and president of the Basketball Federation.
